===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*mey- (change)}}
[[File:Zenith-Nadir-Horizon.svg|thumb|300px|right|Diagram showing the relationship between the '''zenith''', the [[nadir]], and different types of [[horizon]]. Note that the '''zenith''' is opposite the nadir.]]
From {{inh|en|enm|cenyth}}, from {{der|en|ML.|cenit}}, from {{der|en|ar|سَمْت||direction, path}}, from the fuller form {{m|ar|سَمْت اَلرَّأْس||direction of the head}}. The ''-ni-'' for ''-m-'' is sometimes thought to be due to a misreading of the three strokes, which is plausible, though it could be a mere phonetic approximation.

